# TreeDB Production Hardening + TreeSeed SDK Integration Plan

Status: Draft  
Owner: TreeDB / TreeSeed platform team  
Scope: `treeseed-ai/treedb` and `packages/ts-sdk`  
Target: Production-ready TreeDB service plus stable TreeSeed SDK remote TreeDB mode  
Baseline: TreeDB MVP snapshot, 2026-06-02

---

## 1. Executive Summary

TreeDB is already a strong MVP: it has a Phoenix API service, Rust-backed native storage/Git/graph crates, TreeDB-native `.tdb` records, scoped auth/capabilities, workspace file operations, overlay commits, repository query APIs, graph/context endpoints, snapshots/artifacts, mirrors, migrations, audit, and opt-in TypeScript SDK TreeDB clients/adapters.

This plan finishes TreeDB production hardening and completes its integration into the TreeSeed SDK as a stable, no-clone, repository-native transport.

The production goal is:

> TreeDB lets workers, agents, SDKs, and applications safely manage, query, index, snapshot, mirror, federate, and mutate Git repository portfolios without local clones, while preserving Git-native semantics, strong authorization, auditable operations, and clear separation from TreeSeed product-domain concepts.

