# 10. Risk Register

| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |
|---|---|---|
| JWKS/control-plane auth is under-specified | Production auth weakness | Build verifier abstraction and fail-closed boot config |
| Direct exec sandbox leaks host data | Critical security issue | Require production sandbox backend and isolation tests |
| Federation leaks hidden data through ranking/counts | Cross-tenant data leak | Query only authorized segments before ranking/serialization |
| Storage corruption loses metadata | Data loss | Data-dir lock, checksums, recovery mode, backup/restore |
| SDK remote mode breaks local SDK ergonomics | Adoption blocker | Keep local mode default and add parity tests |
| API/server and SDK type drift | Runtime failures | OpenAPI drift checks and SDK contract tests |
| Git push leaks credentials | Secret exposure | Credential provider boundary and URL sanitizer |
| Policy revocation does not affect active workspaces | Unauthorized access persists | Workspace policy hash and quarantine/expire flow |
| Product semantics creep into TreeDB | Architecture degradation | Keep model registry/product mapping in SDK/core |
| Shell Git fallback becomes default | Reliability/security drift | Track every fallback and prefer gix implementation |

